<p>I'm using itextsharp to read alot of pdfs. Every things works create expect, sometimes the reader adds whitespaces in words. Example:</p>  <p>S am D ar k a tsh<br> A nal yst   </p>  <p>Gary Chase<br> Analyst</p>  <p>is there any option to get rid of this?</p>  <p>thanks</p>  <p>EDIT:</p>  <pre><code>for (int i = 1; i &lt; reader.NumberOfPages; i++) {     listener = parser.ProcessContent(i, new RenderListener());     listener.TextItems.ForEach(o =&gt; list.Add(o)); } </code></pre>  <p>My RenderListener:</p>  <pre><code>public class RenderListener : IRenderListener {     public List&lt;TextItem&gt; TextItems = new List&lt;TextItem&gt;();      public void RenderText(TextRenderInfo renderInfo)     {          var text = renderInfo.GetText(); // &lt;-- whitespaces in here     } } </code></pre>